  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> and chop roughly, discarding the stems&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to one side of a baking tray</p>\r\n<p>Sprinkle with half of the <strong>chopped rosemary </strong>(save the rest for later!)&nbsp;and drizzle generously with&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and put the tray in the oven for 10 min (until approx. step 4)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile,&nbsp;peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> fennel seeds</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span><strong> black pepper</strong>&nbsp;and a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>to a <strong>pestle and mortar</strong>&nbsp;and grind to a course spice mixture</p>\r\n<p>Add half of the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, the remaining <strong>rosemary </strong>and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil </strong>and mix to combine - this is your <strong>fennel paste</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>onion</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Remove the <strong>potatoes&nbsp;</strong>from the oven and add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> to the other side of the tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Spread the<strong>&nbsp;fennel paste</strong> all over the <strong>pork tenderloins</strong>&nbsp;and sit them on&nbsp;the<strong> sliced onion</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-18 min or until cooked through</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/55_step-4-x200.jpg",
